### Customer Service Campaign API — sample requests
@baseUrl = https://localhost:7227

### 1. Get a bearer token
# @name token
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/auth/token
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "clientId": "crm-demo",
  "clientSecret": "crm-demo-secret"
}

### 2. Look a customer up in the external SOAP directory
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/customers/1
Authorization: Bearer {{token.response.body.accessToken}}

### 3. Create a reward (the agent's form)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/rewards
Authorization: Bearer {{token.response.body.accessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "agentUsername": "viktor",
  "customerId": 1,
  "discountPercent": 15
}

### 4. List rewards
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/rewards?agentUsername=viktor
Authorization: Bearer {{token.response.body.accessToken}}

### 5. Correct a mistake (replace {id})
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/rewards/{id}
Authorization: Bearer {{token.response.body.accessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "discountPercent": 25
}

### 6. Remove a mistaken entry (replace {id})
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/rewards/{id}
Authorization: Bearer {{token.response.body.accessToken}}

### 7. Import the monthly purchase report (use Swagger UI for the file upload)
### samples/purchases-sample.csv

### 8. Campaign results (the merged report)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/reports/campaign-results
Authorization: Bearer {{token.response.body.accessToken}}